      • writeHeader

        protected void writeHeader(TGOutputStream os)
                    throws TGException,
                           java.io.IOException
        The Server describes the pdu header as below. struct _tg_pduheader_t_ { tg_int32 length; //length of the message including the header tg_int32 magic; //Magic to recognize this is our message tg_int16 protVersion; //protocol version tg_pduverb verbId; //we write the verb as a short value tg_uint64 sequenceNo; //message Sequence No from the client tg_uint64 timestamp; //Timestamp of the message sent. tg_uint64 requestId; //Unique _request Identifier from the client, which is returned tg_int32 dataOffset; //Offset from where the payload begins }
        Parameters:
